text: is a moon of Jupiter. It was found by a team of astronomers led by Brett J. Gladman in 2003.IAUC 8116: Satellites of Jupiter and Saturn 2003 April 11 (discovery)MPEC 2003-G18: S/2003 J 16 2003 April 3 (discovery and ephemeris) is about 2 kilometres in diameter, and orbits Jupiter at an average distance of 20,744,000 km in 610.362 days, at an inclination of 151° to the ecliptic (149° to Jupiter's equator), with an orbital eccentricity of 0.3185. It belongs to the Ananke group, retrograde non-spherical moons which orbit Jupiter between 19,300,000 and 22,700,000 km, at inclinations of about 150°. ==References== Category:Jupiter's moons
